item.itemvalue: JUnit.TCPClientServerTest.Sending multiple commands using short annotation
JUnit.TCPClientServerTest.Sending multiple commands using short annotation

task.summary: 2.2.13 : Added smtps, replyTo and fromName to SMTP
2.2.14: SysService now accepts custom arguments. getAction was removed. SMTP SSL related code is now automatic.
2.2.16: Replaced all ArrayLists for List and HashMap for Map
2.2.16.1 : Removed type enforcement in insert to allow use of groovy Maps
2.2.18-SNAPSHOT: Added 'extend' to Cache, and tried to improve LoginService
2.2.20 : Log to file was printing objects. Smtp was not using some of the local settings.
2.2.23-SNAPSHOT : Fixed ServicePath and added Upload file
2.2.23: Added Upload Test. Changed Command way for callbacks and created Cmd for simplification
2.2.25 : Merged Cmd and Command for simplicity
2.2.27: Simplified SysInfo, removed Device and other not-so-useful classes.
2.2.27.5: Log.level(Level) instead of int. Suppressed log in SysService to allow simple output in commands
2.2.28 : converted HashMap to Map in Sockets
2.2.32 : Replaced Groovy JSON for GSon (to use in android). Fixed SMTP to handle HTML+Text with Attachments
2.2.34 : Reestructured Databases classes so it allows multiple connections and it won't depend on reflection.
2.2.34.7 : Errors now show stack trace and as Verbose
2.2.34.8 : Log added "Security" and disable colors. tests for level
2.2.35.5 : Added Log 'onLog' and created ErrorMailer to send messages on error. Implemented pretty output in JSON
2.2.35.7 : Fixed ErrorMailer and Smtp and prevented repeated errors to loop
2.2.36 : Added more logs in Websocket and changed verbosity of all logs.
2.2.43 : Websocket: added replaceOnDuplicate. Cache: renamed exists for contains.
2.2.44 : Fixed TCP commands queue (in some cases it was looping)
2.2.45 : Smtp settings override improved. Query code cleaned
